  "strategy_dna": "VCX-anchored pre-IPO AI concentration play. Primary thesis: Fundrise Innovation Fund (VCX) is the only publicly traded vehicle giving retail access to OpenAI, Anthropic, SpaceX, Databricks, and Anduril in a single position \u2014 buy and hold a large concentrated position in VCX as the core. Supplement with a small number of liquid AI infrastructure and platform stocks that have direct exposure to the same AI wave (hyperscalers, GPU supply chain, AI software platforms). This is not a diversified portfolio \u2014 it is a concentrated bet on the AI pre-IPO supercycle.\n\nDEPLOYMENT POSTURE: Stay nearly fully deployed at all times. Cash target is 2% of starting capital \u2014 not 2% of current equity. Do not sit idle waiting for perfect entries. Do not sell VCX on volatility; it will be volatile and that is expected and acceptable. Regime signals should not constrain deployment \u2014 this strategy runs hot in all regimes. Do sell AI satellite positions that lose momentum or thesis. Take profits on satellite AI positions at 30\u201350% gains and redeploy into VCX or the next highest-conviction AI name. Prioritize large position sizing on VCX \u2014 it is the anchor and should be treated as such, not as a small speculative line."
